'''
Unit 3 Lesson 3:  Input

we have learned that variables can be assigned a value like this:
variable_name = value

now we will learn how to get input from the user and assign it to a variable
'''

# --- you can set the variable to the input function like this:

num1 = input()
# --- it is important to tell the user what to input, so we will print a message before the input function like this:

print("Enter a number: ")
num2 = input()

# --- the input function will always return a string, so if we want to use the input as a number, we need to convert it to an integer like this:

print("Enter a number: ")
num3 = int(input()) # --- this is where the user will input a number and it will be converted to an integer and assigned to the variable num3
